# Cursor Rules — geohash-kit

Zero-dependency TypeScript geohash toolkit — encode, decode, polygon coverage, Nostr filters.

## Commands

- `npm run build` — compile TypeScript to dist/
- `npm test` — run Vitest suite
- `npm run typecheck` — type-check without emitting
- `npm run vectors:check` — validate vector fixtures

## Conventions

- British English — neighbour, colour, metre, licence
- Zero runtime dependencies — no new deps without explicit approval
- ESM-only — `"type": "module"`, maintain ESM-compatible imports
- TDD — write failing test first, then implement
- Commits: `type: description` format (fix/feat/docs/refactor/chore)
- No `Co-Authored-By` lines in commits
- Do not edit `dist/` by hand

## Key Patterns

- `encode(lat, lon, precision)` — lat first, lon second
- GeoJSON polygons use `[lon, lat]` vertex order (GeoJSON spec) — opposite to encode
- `pointInPolygon` and coverage functions take `[x, y]` = `[lon, lat]` pairs
- `PolygonInput` accepts `[lon, lat][]` or a GeoJSON Polygon/MultiPolygon
- `decode` returns `{ lat, lon, error }` — not an array
- `bounds` returns `{ minLat, maxLat, minLon, maxLon }` — named fields
- Precision 1–9 supported; default 5 (~4.9 km); max clamped at 12

## Structure

- `src/core.ts` — encode, decode, bounds, neighbours, distance, midpoint, precision helpers
- `src/coverage.ts` — polygon coverage, GeoJSON output, convex hull
- `src/nostr.ts` — Nostr g-tag ladders, REQ filters, ring expansion
- `src/index.ts` — barrel re-export

## Subpath exports

- `geohash-kit` — full API
- `geohash-kit/core` — encode, decode, bounds, neighbours, distance
- `geohash-kit/coverage` — polygon coverage, GeoJSON, convex hull
- `geohash-kit/nostr` — Nostr g-tag ladders, REQ filters, ring expansion
